docs.lead_paragraph: To the Editor of the New. York Daily Times: The highly interesting sketch of Judge CADY, published in your paper a few days since, induces me to send you the following characteristic reminiscence of that truly eminent man. The anecdote was related to me by a noted lawyer, a personal and political friend of the Judge, who was present on the occasion. ustrates

docs.lead_paragraph: The steamship Star of the West, of the Nicaragua line, E. W. TURNER Commander, arrived last evening from Punta Arenas, via Key West, with passengers and $640,000 in specie on freight to C. MORGAN. To Purser LORD, and Messrs. WELLS, FARGO Co., and W. ADAMS Co. We are obliged for favors.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Board of Ten Governors held a regular meeting yesterday afternoon. present, all the members except GOVS. HERRICK and HENRY. A communication was received from the Superintendent of the Workhouse, recommending the establishment of a library in the institution under his charge. GOV. TIEMAN moved an appropriation of $500 for that purpose, but after some consideration the subject was referred to the Committee on the Workhouse to report.
